30|$|However, <b>prophylactic</b> <b>antibiotics</b> are {{commonly}} administered for the TVT procedure based on empirical grounds [1]. Postoperative {{infection in the}} “clean-contaminated” [6] TVT surgical field carries the ominous hazard of spreading to the neighbouring tissues and forming pelvic abscesses. Hence, as widely recommended for operations similar to the TVT that involve potential exposure to bacteriologic pathogens [7 – 16], <b>prophylactic</b> <b>antibiotics</b> are used routinely to minimise the possibility of TVT-related infections. Reported here are three patients diagnosed with post-TVT surgical field infections [17]. The issue of <b>prophylactic</b> <b>antibiotics</b> in the TVT procedure is discussed.|$|R
